import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', bins=30, color='blue', kde=True)
    median_delay = data['delay'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_delay, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Delay: {median_delay:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Delay Time')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    average_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    ax = sns.barplot(x=['Average Distance'], y=[average_distance], palette='viridis')
    ax.axhline(average_distance, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {average_distance:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average distance traveled by flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['route'] = data['origin'] + '-' + data['destination']
    route_counts = data['route'].value_counts().reset_index()
    route_counts.columns = ['route', 'count']

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='route', y='count', data=route_counts.head(10), palette='viridis')
    plt.title('Which origin and destination airports have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Origin-Destination')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Top 10 Routes', loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='distance', y='delay', hue='origin', palette='deep')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between delay time and distance?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Delay')
    plt.legend(title='Origin', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.dates as mdates

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    data['date'] = data['date'].dt.to_period('M')
    date_counts = data['date'].value_counts().sort_index()
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.lineplot(x=date_counts.index.to_timestamp(), y=date_counts.values, ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.set_title('Distribution of Flight Dates', wrap=True)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%b %Y'))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
